    "updated_at": "2016-12-17T22:51:49Z",
    "body": "> This is expected, because an offscreen window behaves like a frameless window\r\n\r\nIf that's the case, shouldn’t I get the same results for off- vs. on-screen if I instantiate the window with `useContentSize`? e.g:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst window = new electron.BrowserWindow({\r\n  width: 500,\r\n  height: 500,\r\n  useContentSize: true,\r\n  webPreferences: {\r\n    offscreen: type === 'offscreen'\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn that case, the measurements still differ by the size of the window chrome."
  },
